{{Unreferenced|article|date=December 2009}}
A '''rapporteur''' is a person who is appointed by an organization to report on the proceedings of its meetings.
For example, [[Dick Marty]] was appointed ''rapporteur'' by the [[Parliamentary Assembly of the Council of Europe]] to investigate [[extraordinary rendition]] by the [[CIA]].
Authors of reports prepared by [[Standing Committees of the European Parliament|committees of the European Parliament]] are also known as "rapporteurs". Authors of reports assisting a rapporteur in preparation of [[Standing Committees of the European Parliament|committees of the European Parliament]] are known as '''shadow rapporteurs''', and may vary in number depending on the scope of the issue.
==See also== *[[Special rapporteur (disambiguation)|Special rapporteur]] *[[United Nations special rapporteur]]
